<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2018-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>3 Loss of Biological Diversity and Emergence of Infectious Diseases</TITLE><BODY>Abstract: Abiotic factors, climatic factors (such as temperature and rainfall) and biotic factors (such as population density and the structure of host communities and reservoirs) are essential variables in the transmission of infectious or parasitic agents.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>